00:08:24.133 --> 00:08:29.667
Yeah. The song I was singing
is titled Ubuhle Bomhlaba

00:08:29.667 --> 00:08:35.633
meaning the beauty of our land,
or may I say the beauty of our country.

00:08:35.633 --> 00:08:38.934
Here it wasn't only just singing about
the beauty of my country or the land,

00:08:38.934 --> 00:08:46.100
but also about quite a lot of things which
were very disturbing and very sad you know.

00:08:46.100 --> 00:08:50.900
To sort of like really witness that through
the time when it was really quite a lot of time

00:08:50.900 --> 00:08:58.333
when in, in South Africa and Apartheid
where we also witnessed the police brutality,

00:08:58.333 --> 00:09:03.900
police playing with our dead corpses,
thinking that we don't know about it is;

00:09:03.900 --> 00:09:09.633
and here in this song I'm saying we will call
them and teach them about those corpses;

00:09:09.633 --> 00:09:13.066
and if they agree we will forgive them.

00:09:13.066 --> 00:09:16.934
But if they don't, we will expose them.

00:09:16.934 --> 00:09:20.166
And of course this was written long
before we were putting that to work

00:09:20.166 --> 00:09:26.367
or going to have you know the truth and
reconciliation in South Africa, if you remember.

00:09:26.367 --> 00:09:30.467
The truth and reconciliation were just
something that of course it was championed

00:09:30.467 --> 00:09:32.700
by our grandfathers of humanity,

00:09:32.700 --> 00:09:35.934
Archbishop Desmond Tutu;

00:09:35.934 --> 00:09:39.934
people who also were talking
about the wisdom of forgiveness:

00:09:39.934 --> 00:09:42.834
Archbishop Desmond Tutu,
Dr. Nelson Mandela

00:09:42.834 --> 00:09:45.834
and the man who lived in South Africa
many years

00:09:45.834 --> 00:09:51.567
and planted a seed of reconciliation,
Mr. Mahatma Ghandi.

00:09:51.567 --> 00:09:56.967
These are the grandfathers of humanity who
taught us that there is wisdom in forgiveness.

00:09:56.967 --> 00:10:00.967
That if you learn to forgive you
learn more to be free.

00:10:00.967 --> 00:10:04.867
You know to [inaudible] calmness within the
inner most of yourself and become more free.

00:10:04.867 --> 00:10:07.967
But if you don't forgive,
you are your own prisoner.

00:10:07.967 --> 00:10:11.367
If you don't forgive you are the one
who's suffering the most.

00:10:11.367 --> 00:10:14.133
You will become like a bitter leaf
that can just be squashed

00:10:14.133 --> 00:10:16.233
or be swept away by the wind anytime.

00:10:16.233 --> 00:10:21.100
So forgiveness is very important and
we should all wear it like a crown.

00:10:21.100 --> 00:10:22.400
