00:54:38.333 --> 00:54:44.967
Vusi Mahlasela: Yeah. I think it, it is very much important that

00:54:44.967 --> 00:54:49.734
the youth today of course there's quite a lot of
things that they are really checking out,

00:54:49.734 --> 00:54:55.000
taking especially through technology which is, and the music that they are making

00:54:55.000 --> 00:54:57.300
with some of the effects and everything
that they do,

00:54:57.300 --> 00:55:02.433
but I think to check where the raw thing
comes from is very much important.

00:55:02.433 --> 00:55:06.633
Not only just about the music and then
perhaps the indigenous instruments

00:55:06.633 --> 00:55:09.000
which are sort of accompanying
or something like that,

00:55:09.000 --> 00:55:13.133
but I think the message as well
is very much important.

00:55:13.133 --> 00:55:17.200
I think building up on that is like
after the post-Apartheid South Africa,

00:55:17.200 --> 00:55:21.600
what I've witnessed is wild
and in sort of like a, the,

00:55:21.600 --> 00:55:25.700
some kind of you know the ignorance
that you see in the youth forgetting

00:55:25.700 --> 00:55:30.300
that the privileges and the rights
that they enjoy, they didn't just come by -

00:55:30.300 --> 00:55:31.667
people fought for and died for.

00:55:31.667 --> 00:55:35.400
And therefore they need some kind
of a counter revolution in some way.

00:55:35.400 --> 00:55:40.200
And songs that say something about
where we come from,

00:55:40.200 --> 00:55:44.000
how it had been so as to
make love today the future

00:55:44.000 --> 00:55:46.533
is very much important that they hear this.

00:55:46.533 --> 00:55:53.367
And it, it's, with what I'm doing as well
going to, to schools and colleges

00:55:53.367 --> 00:55:57.967
and everything where the students are asking
questions and everything wanting to know,

00:55:57.967 --> 00:56:04.300
it is very much important because art, music it's very power.

00:56:04.300 --> 00:56:11.467
Through music you can sort of like really
bring out things that you want to address

00:56:11.467 --> 00:56:13.967
whereas other people are afraid to say it.

00:56:13.967 --> 00:56:17.266
But with the music you say it and freely without,

00:56:17.266 --> 00:56:20.633
or write whatever you like and nobody
sort of like,

00:56:20.633 --> 00:56:21.900
"No, you don't have to write that and do it."

00:56:21.900 --> 00:56:26.100
And when people see you doing that they're,
