00:58:28.567 --> 00:58:29.800
My name is Dennis.

00:58:29.800 --> 00:58:32.533
I work with Google in the Nairobi office

00:58:32.533 --> 00:58:38.166
and I'm very passionate about
the role of language

00:58:38.166 --> 00:58:39.600
in the adoption of technology.

00:58:39.600 --> 00:58:44.500
So as a follow up to the question
about the role of music,

00:58:44.500 --> 00:58:49.867
and music in, in indigenous languages and how you express that

00:58:49.867 --> 00:58:52.834
and how that sort of gets people
into the struggle and that sort of thing.

00:58:52.834 --> 00:58:58.834
What, what do you see as the role
of local languages like Soto and

00:58:58.834 --> 00:59:03.300
so on getting more people
in South Africa to use technology,

00:59:03.300 --> 00:59:06.734
to use the Internet,

00:59:06.734 --> 00:59:11.633
to express themselves and participate
more freely on the Internet?

00:59:11.633 --> 00:59:18.333
Vusi Mahlasela: Yeah. It is important
that people take proud,

00:59:18.333 --> 00:59:21.166
I mean take pride in what they are

00:59:21.166 --> 00:59:24.133
and especially in the language
that they speak.

00:59:24.133 --> 00:59:28.467
It was this African idiom which says
[speaking native language]

00:59:28.467 --> 00:59:32.166
which means a person is a language.

00:59:32.166 --> 00:59:36.467
And if you learn to speak other people's
language we learn more to understand them,

00:59:36.467 --> 00:59:40.433
to know them, to know their culture
and to love them.

00:59:40.433 --> 00:59:43.734
So language plays quite a lot of
important role in the society.

00:59:43.734 --> 00:59:49.767
And when you put a different language
in a song

00:59:49.767 --> 00:59:51.867
and then also collaborate and sing
with other people,

00:59:51.867 --> 00:59:54.867
we teach each other and
then it is like not about hate whatever;

00:59:54.867 --> 00:59:58.900
just to pick a safe song and people
are sort of like,

00:59:58.900 --> 01:00:01.233
"What language are you singing about
and what it is about?"

01:00:01.233 --> 01:00:02.767
And it's really hard.

01:00:02.767 --> 01:00:08.867
I read another book where the song lines
about from Aus--,

01:00:08.867 --> 01:00:13.533
it's about Australia and the aboriginal
languages where they have,

01:00:13.533 --> 01:00:18.300
they had this thing whereby
when you're traveled you learned.

01:00:18.300 --> 01:00:21.867
They teach you a song in another
language and you have to travel

01:00:21.867 --> 01:00:24.734
until you come to a certain point
at another border;

01:00:24.734 --> 01:00:27.166
you get another people there,

01:00:27.166 --> 01:00:29.734
they will teach you another song
in another language.

01:00:29.734 --> 01:00:35.033
So it teaches you how to travel in a way
you can get water to drink in the wells,

01:00:35.033 --> 01:00:38.133
but if you cannot study or learn the song,

01:00:38.133 --> 01:00:40.533
you won't be able to travel.
You will get lost.

01:00:40.533 --> 01:00:43.800
So you always have to, to learn
the language and different languages

01:00:43.800 --> 01:00:44.700
everywhere you travel.

01:00:44.700 --> 01:00:47.367
So you see that the language plays
very much important role

01:00:47.367 --> 01:00:51.633
and there was a must that you have to learn
the language so that you may be able to travel.

01:00:51.633 --> 01:00:53.200
And I think this is what we need.

01:00:53.200 --> 01:00:54.533
Through technology and everything

01:00:54.533 --> 01:00:58.667
whatever just for that the language
that we can all like.

01:01:01.734 --> 01:01:04.800
Yeah. That's where immigrating
into a group or village,

01:01:04.800 --> 01:01:07.900
the question is how much
do you want to belong?

01:01:07.900 --> 01:01:12.300
I think the thing that will play important role
is the language that we have to learn,

01:01:12.300 --> 01:01:15.567
each other's language and that way,
that way we can get by.

